'''Mathieu Choinière''' (born February 7, 1999) is a Canadian professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]], [[defensive midfielder]] or [[right winger]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Los Angeles FC]] and the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
Choinière was born in [[Saint-Jean-sur-Richelieu, Quebec]] and grew up in the neighbouring [[Saint-Alexandre, Quebec]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/profile/?id=4293&teamId=2078|title=Mathieu Choinière Canada Soccer Profile|work=[[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref> He began playing soccer with [[Celtix du Haut-Richelieu]], before moving on to [[CS St-Hubert]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arsrs.com/fr/publication/nouvelle/mathieu_choiniere_signe_son_premier_contrat_pro_avec_limpact.html|title=Mathieu Choinière Signe Son Premier Contrat Pro avec L'Impact|trans-title=Mathieu Choinière Signs His First Pro Contract with the Impact|language=fr|date=July 18, 2018|work=ARS Rive-Sud|access-date=August 19, 2021|archive-date=April 25, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230425214055/http://www.arsrs.com/fr/publication/nouvelle/mathieu_choiniere_signe_son_premier_contrat_pro_avec_limpact.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2011, he joined the [[Montreal Impact Academy]] and became the first player in the organization's history to play for the U13, U14, U16, U18 and U19 teams prior to joining the first team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvasports.ca/2021/07/27/mathieu-choiniere-reve-maintenant-de-marquer-a-montreal-1|title=Mathieu Choinière Rêve Maintenant de Marquer à Montréal|trans-title=Mathieu Choinière Now Dreams of Scoring in Montreal|language=fr|date=July 27, 2021|first=Benoit|last=Rioux|work=[[TVA Sports]]}}</ref>

== Club career ==
=== CF Montréal ===
Choinière signed an MLS contract with the [[CF Montréal|Montreal Impact]], later renamed [[CF Montréal]], on July 17, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.impactmontreal.com/en/post/2018/07/17/mathieu-choini%C3%A8re-signs-mls-contract-impact|publisher=Montreal Impact|title=Mathieu Choinière signs an MLS contract with the Impact|accessdate=July 23, 2016}}</ref> He made his first appearance the next day against the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] in the [[Canadian Championship]]. He made his first league appearance 3 days later against the [[Portland Timbers]]. Choinière would have his option for the 2020 season exercised by the Impact, keeping him with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.impactmontreal.com/en/post/2019/11/21/impact-exercises-options-11-players|title=Impact exercises options for 11 players|website=Montreal Impact|date=November 21, 2019}}</ref> In February 2022 Choinière signed a contract extension through 2024, with an option year for 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/cf-montreal-and-mathieu-choiniere-agree-to-two-year-contract-extension|title=CF Montréal and Mathieu Choinière agree to two-year contract extension|date=February 26, 2022|work=[[CF Montréal]]}}</ref> In June 2023, he was named to the [[2023 MLS All-Star Game]] team after a standout first half of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/cf-montreal-midfielder-mathieu-choiniere-named-to-mls-all-star-game-1.1978007|title=CFMTL's Choiniere named to MLS All-Star Game|date=June 27, 2023|work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/2023-mls-all-star-mathieu-choiniere/|title=Choiniere Is An MLS All-Star, So Why Didn't Canada Call Him Up?|first=John|last=Jacques|date=June 27, 2023|work=Northern Tribune}}</ref> During the [[2024 Major League Soccer season|2024 season]], Choinière was once again named an [[2024 MLS All-Star Game|MLS All-Star]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/mathieu-choiniere-selected-for-2024-mls-all-star-game|date=July 1, 2024|title=Mathieu Choinière selected for 2024 MLS All-Star Game|work=[[CF Montréal]]}}</ref>

=== Grasshoppers ===
On 27 August 2024, Choinière made the jump into European football, signing a three-year contract with [[Swiss Super League]] side [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshoppers]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]]|url=https://www.gcz.ch/en/news/article/1/gc-zurich-signs-central-midfielder-mathieu-choiniere/|title=GC Zurich signs central midfielder Mathieu Choinière|date=27 August 2024|access-date=27 August 2024|language=en}}</ref> He made his debut for his new club on 21 September 2024 against [[Servette FC|Servette]], and scored the first goal in an eventual 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gcz.ch/news/artikel/1/unentschieden-gegen-servette/|date=September 21, 2024|title=UNENTSCHIEDEN GEGEN SERVETTE|work=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshoppers]]}}</ref>

=== Los Angeles FC ===
On 28 July 2025, he was loaned to Grasshoppers' parent club [[Los Angeles FC]] until the end of 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title= LAFC Acquires Midfielder Mathieu Choinière On Loan From Grasshopper Club Zürich |url=https://www.lafc.com/news/lafc-acquires-midfielder-mathieu-choiniere-on-loan-from-grasshopper-club-zurich|publisher=[[Los Angeles FC]] |access-date=28 July 2025 |language=en-us |date=28 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mathieu Choinière per Leihe zu LAFC|url=https://www.gcz.ch/news/artikel/1/mathieu-choiniere-per-leihe-zu-lafc/ |publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |access-date=28 July 2025 |language=de-ch |date=28 July 2025}}</ref> On 9 December 2025, LAFC exercised their buy option to sign Choinière permanently.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mathieu Choinière wechselt fest zum LAFC|url=https://www.gcz.ch/news/artikel/1/mathieu-choiniere-wechselt-fest-zum-lafc/ |publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |access-date=12 December 2025 |language=de-ch |date=9 December 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=LAFC Exercises Permanent Transfer On Midfielder Mathieu Choinière |url=https://www.lafc.com/news/lafc-exercises-permanent-transfer-on-midfielder-mathieu-choiniere|publisher=[[Los Angeles FC]] |access-date=12 December 2025 |language=en-us |date=9 December 2025}}</ref>

== International career ==
===Youth===
Choinière has been called up to various youth camps for [[Canada]].<ref>{{Canada Soccer player|4293}}</ref> In 2017, he was called up to a Quebec-Canada U20 team to play friendlies against [[Haiti national under-20 football team|Haiti U20]], who were preparing for the [[Football at the 2017 Jeux de la Francophonie|2017 Jeux de la Francophonie]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvasports.ca/2017/07/07/limpact-u18-bien-represente-dans-la-selection-canada-quebec|title=L'Impact U18 Bien Représenté dans la Sélection Canada-Québec|language=fr|work=[[TVA Sports]]|date=July 7, 2017|trans-title=The Impact U18 Well Represented in the Canada-Quebec Selection}}</ref> In May 2018, he was called up to the Canada U21 team for the [[2018 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wakingthered.com/2018/5/17/17366008/canadas-roster-toulon-tournament-2018-france-liam-millar|title=Canada's next generation will be on display at the Toulon Tournament|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney|date=May 17, 2018|access-date=August 5, 2018|archive-date=July 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707100611/https://www.wakingthered.com/2018/5/17/17366008/canadas-roster-toulon-tournament-2018-france-liam-millar|url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored a goal against [[France national under-20 football team|France]] in the fifth-place playoff.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-place-6th-at-prestigious-toulon-tournament-in-france-p161608|title=Canada place 6th at prestigious Toulon tournament in France|date=June 7, 2018|access-date=August 5, 2018|archive-date=January 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117010925/https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-place-6th-at-prestigious-toulon-tournament-in-france-p161608|url-status=dead}}</ref> In October 2018 Choinière was named to the [[Canada men's national under-20 soccer team|Canadian Under-20]] squad for the [[2018 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-announces-squad-for-the-concacaf-men-s-under-20-championship-p161897|title=Canada announces squad for the Concacaf Men's Under-20 Championship|date=October 24, 2018|access-date=October 29, 2018|archive-date=May 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502140910/https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-announces-squad-for-the-concacaf-men-s-under-20-championship-p161897|url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored in Canada's second game of the tournament against Guadeloupe.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/soccer/article-canada-beats-guadeloupe-at-mens-concacaf-u20-championship/|date=November 4, 2018|title=Canada beats Guadeloupe at men's CONCACAF U20 championship|website=[[The Globe and Mail]] }}</ref> Choinière was named to the [[Canada men's national under-23 soccer team|Canadian U-23]] provisional roster for the [[2020 CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualifying Championship]] on February 26, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Canada Soccer announces Provisional List for Concacaf Men's Olympic Qualifying |url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-soccer-announces-provisional-list-for-concacaf-men-s-olympic-qualifying-p162594-preview-1 |publisher=Canada Soccer |accessdate=February 26, 2020 |date=February 26, 2020 |archive-date=March 9, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309191149/https://www.canadasoccer.com/canada-soccer-announces-provisional-list-for-concacaf-men-s-olympic-qualifying-p162594-preview-1 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===Senior===
In November 2022, Choinière received his first call-up to the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canadian]] senior side for a friendly against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/eight-cf-montreal-players-called-up-for-canadian-national-team-training-camp|title=Eight CF Montréal players called up for Canadian national team training camp|date=November 2, 2022|work=[[CF Montréal]]}}</ref> but did not feature in the match. On October 13, 2023, Choinière made his debut for Canada in a friendly against [[Japan national football team|Japan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/choiniere-and-paton-make-their-canada-debuts/|date=October 13, 2023|title=Choinière and Paton make their Canada debut away against Japan|work=[[Canada Soccer Association]]}}</ref> coming on as a substitute for [[Jonathan Osorio]] at the 61st minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CanadaSoccerEN/status/1712800191424676200|date=October 13, 2023|title=Mathieu Choinière comes on for Jonathan Osorio|work=[[Canada Soccer Association]]}}</ref>

In June 2024, Choinière  was named to Canada's 26-man squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/canmnt-announce-2024-copa-america-roster/|title=CANMNT ANNOUNCE 2024 COPA AMÉRICA ROSTER|date=June 15, 2024|work= [[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Choinière is of [[Filipinos|Filipino descent]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gangué-Ruzic |first1=Alexandre |title='I'm happy to be a role model': For CPL players, Asian Heritage Month represents chance to reflect, look forward |url=https://canpl.ca/article/im-happy-to-be-a-role-model-for-cpl-players-asian-heritage-month-represents-chance-to-reflect-look-forward |access-date=15 October 2024}}</ref> His older brother [[David Choinière|David]] is also a soccer player.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/champions-league/news/david-and-mathieu-choiniere-a-tale-of-brothers-in-the-sccl/|title=David and Mathieu Choiniere: A tale of brothers in the SCCL|date=February 15, 2022|work=[[CONCACAF]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://forgefc.canpl.ca/article/battle-of-the-choiniere-brothers-adds-extra-spice-to-canadian-championship-opening-leg-against-cf-montreal-in-forges-school-day-match|title=Battle of the Choiniére brothers adds extra spice to Canadian Championship opening leg against CF Montréal in Forge's School Day Match|date=May 6, 2024|first=Steve|last=Milton|work=[[Forge FC]]}}</ref>

